
.TH "JSON-VIEW" "1" "May 2025" "json-view @PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
json-view \- terminal JSON viewer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B json-view
.RI [ FILE\ .\|.\|. ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B json-view
displays JSON data in a navigable tree using the
.BR ncurses (3x)
library.  If no
.I FILE
is provided the program reads a single document from standard input.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h , --help
Show usage information.
.TP
.B -V , --version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.B -p , --parse-only
Pretty-print input JSON and exit.
.TP
.B --validate
Validate JSON input and exit with a status code.
.TP
.B --no-mouse
Disable mouse support and rely on keyboard input only.
